# RQ-53-20-03-101: Two-Bay Crack Criteria

## Requirement Statement
A crack in the BWB outer skin panel shall not propagate beyond two frame bays before detection by scheduled inspection.

## Rationale
Fail-safe design philosophy ensures time for detection and repair.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Crack growth analysis shows > 2Ã— inspection interval to critical size
- Inspection interval established (C-Check recommended)
- NDT method validated for detection capability

## Compliance Status
Crack growth analysis complete, inspection interval TBD

## Traceability
Parent: CS-25.571, AMC 25.571
